title: Ask HN: How many of those philosophical chaims got debunked by GPT4
text:
For example:

1. Thinking is not computiation.

2. Machine will never understand grammars or natural language.

3. AI cannot make or explain a joke.

4. AI can never be creative.

5. AI can never write a poem.

6. Human's life experience is the key factor be intellegent, and machine cannot have it.

7. Human do not need training to be intelligent, but machine do. So machine is not as smart as human.

8. Human's cognitive ability is not a cumulative work of pattern maching and learning from everyday life.

People used to write serveral thousand of words to explain human magic. How many/much of these chaims still hold?

Ask HN: When hiring, which verifiable secondary/soft skills are a plus to you?
text:
There is no shortage of discussions on direct tech and scientific skills every person working in a tech job should have. There is also no shortage of discussions on the kind of soft skills which are hard to verify or quantify (teamwork, personality, independence etc.).

What about non-essential skills (for the position) that are a bit more verifiable? To give you one example: Would CEFR[1] language certificates (let's say equal to or above C1 level) in multiple languages be something you look upon favourably?

[1]: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Common_European_Framework_of_Reference_for_Languages

Show HN: The Worst of Both – U.S. Politics
text:
Ever wanted to see what both sides of the party lines are saying? This little app I created lets you see them side-by-side.

It pulls from left/right leaning subreddits. You can click on the party logo to pop off the top post, pushing it down to the bottom.

The data is updated roughly every 15 minutes in backend, so you'll need to refresh to get latest on browser.

Ask HN: How can I plant more trees with technology
text:
From past 5 years I have become forest enthusiast. Me and 5 more guys spend weekends planting trees. But it takes a lot time to plant and take care of trees. Because of our limited men-power, I fear, we won't be able to do anything impactful in our lifetime. I would love to know how technology can help in this case.

There's so much innovation happening in other fields but I can't find anything related to Afforestation. This saddens me a little bit.

I am sure there would be more people on HN who are interested in the same area. I would love to hear from you.

Any information around tooling, robotics. Any contacts, guidance. Throw any information you might think will be useful!
